<br>
Everyone has different expectations of EQ.  Everyone has different levels of goals (Explorer, Achiever, Social, etc...).   For Sabastian, it's winning or accomplishing things first and receiving due credit.  But, the problem is, he seems to be approaching it the wrong way.  If you want to be like AL or FoH...  The easiest thing would of been to switch servers and build up another character on MM or Veeshan.  And then work to be a part of them.   If you wanted to build a guild on The Zebux that will be better than them, then good luck.  I know we have the number of high calibur/extended play time hour characters that are necessary for such an 'ub4r' guild, but there are too many burned bridges to get them all to see eye to eye.  Not only that, but I would have to say there is no dominant &quot;Leader&quot; that everyone would respect and trust with their lives.<br>
<br>
That leaves the following options:<br>
1)  Keep banging your head against the wall trying to build the impossible (and if you succeed, then more props to you).<br>
2)  Switch servers, start all over and prove your 'leet' skills to the news makers.<br>
3)  Give up and play a 'social' game<br>
4)  Try out another game that might fit your style.  AO is pretty fun when you are actually able to login.<br>
